4. FAIR USE, PRIVACY, AND ANTI-MALWARE POLICY
This software was created with a focus on user experience and respect for privacy. 
The distribution of derivative or modified works of this software that include 
the following practices is expressively PROHIBITED:

a) Abusive Telemetry and Data Collection: The software cannot collect, track, or 
   transmit personal data, usage telemetry, or device information beyond what is 
   strictly necessary for the basic technical operation of the system. The sale, 
   sharing, or assignment of any user data to advertising companies or third 
   parties is strictly prohibited.
b) Invasive Advertisements (Adware): If the developer uses ads to monetize the 
   derivative software, these must respect the user experience. 
   - PROHIBITED: Full-screen ads (aggressive pop-ups/intersticals), ads that 
     forcibly interrupt the user flow, or excessive display of advertising.
   - PERMITTED ONLY: Discreet banners positioned within the interface (desktop 
     or mobile), reward-based ads (where the user chooses to watch to obtain a 
     benefit), or ads displayed at reasonable time intervals that do not degrade 
     usability.

Non-compliance with any sub-clause of this section classifies the derivative 
software as "Code Malware/Adware" and immediately revokes the right of use and 
distribution under this license.

